This query hunts for behavioral patterns associated with Volt Typhoon-style intrusions, including:

Living-off-the-land binaries (LOLBins)
Suspicious remote execution patterns
Credential access behavior
Long-dwell lateral movement
Administrative tool abuse (WMI, PsExec, WinRM)
Low-noise persistence mechanisms

Volt Typhoon activity is typically:

Fileless or low-malware footprint
Legitimate tool abuse
Stealthy lateral movement inside enterprise networks
Minimal outbound C2 usage (often proxy-based or direct connections)


index=endpoint OR index=security OR index=sysmon
(
    EventCode=4688 OR EventCode=1 OR EventCode=7045 OR EventCode=4624 OR EventCode=4769
)
(
    Image="*cmd.exe"
    OR Image="*powershell.exe"
    OR Image="*wmic.exe"
    OR Image="*psexec*"
    OR Image="*svchost.exe"
    OR Image="*rundll32.exe"
    OR Image="*regsvr32.exe"
    OR Image="*schtasks.exe"
    OR Image="*winrm*"
)
| eval suspicious_activity=case(
    like(CommandLine,"%Invoke-Expression%"), "PowerShell Injection",
    like(CommandLine,"%EncodedCommand%"), "Encoded PowerShell",
    like(Image,"%wmic%"), "WMI Remote Execution",
    like(Image,"%psexec%"), "PsExec Lateral Movement",
    like(Image,"%schtasks%"), "Scheduled Task Persistence",
    like(Image,"%rundll32%"), "Proxy Execution",
    like(Image,"%regsvr32%"), "Script Execution"
)
| stats count values(CommandLine) as commands values(ParentImage) as parents by host user src_ip suspicious_activity
| where count > 3
| sort - count
